Stocks of the following companies
had unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:40 a.m.  The Taiex Index gained 90.98, or 1.1 percent, to 8,373.67.    HTC Corp. (2498)  (2498 TT), the worldâ€™s largest maker of handsets
using Google Inc. and Microsoft Corp. operating systems, jumped
3.5 percent to NT$1,045, set for the highest close since March
10 after it raised a factory budget.  It revised the budget and size of a factory and office
building in its base of Taoyuan, Taiwan, to NT$2.8 billion ($95
million) and 36,483 pings in area, the company said in an
exchange filing yesterday. HTC said in an Oct. 29 filing it
plans to spend NT$1.6 billion for a space of 22,000 pings. One
ping is equal to 3.3 square meters.  Taishin Financial Holding Co. (2887 TT) advanced 1.3
percent to NT$15.95, set for the highest close since March 11.
The company said it will bid for MetLife  Taiwan  Life Insurance
Co. today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
